widgets.default:
This select the way the controller outputs are setup!
This is loaded at boot! Save + Reset Required on change!

In Mirror mode all start at led 0 and do the same.
Max NR of Leds is selected in "Mirror mode NR of Leds" ( MAX 680)
 

In Line mode they are serial. So set the Nr of leds correctly and 
the correct starled for that output. ( MAX 680 SUM of all Lines)

The Maximum FPS ( Max = 90 FPS hard coded) you can get  with 680 leds  depends on the type of leds you use and how many leds are configured here.
If you use only APA102 (680) leds with a datarate of 4 Hz you can get 90 FPS.
If you use only WS2812 (680) leds you will max out at about 40 FPS. (340 Leds = 80 FPS)
The effects you use and the Mix mode selected will also impact the FPS, some are faster others slower.
 

Type : Mode   : led_type  
0: Mix Mirror :     MIX : Data1 + CLk 1 = APA102 ; Data3 = WS2812 ; Data4 = SK8622
5: Mix Line	  :	    MIX : Data1 + CLk 1 = APA102 ; Data3 = WS2812 ; Data4 = SK8622

1: Line   :  APA102 : Data1+CLK & Data3+Data4(clk) = APA102
2: Mirror :  APA102 : Data1+CLK & Data3+Data4(clk) = APA102

3: WS2812b Line   : WS2812b : Data1 to Data4 = WS2812b
4: WS2812b Mirror : WS2812b : Data1 to Data4 = WS2812b


POT Sensetivity
The lower the number the higher the sensititvity. 
but the more likley it is to jump around.

If enabled the TPM will connect to the MQTT server.
 MMQT Topics
 
 The topics are automatically generated

Wifi Hostname/Function/action

 device:  APname / deviceName
 Action: /set = subsribe topic to set something in the TPM
         /status = publish the status of the Function 
 Functions : /device = Is it on or off
              /bri   = Master fader
              /play  = Play nummer / config
              /fps   = Speed

There are 7 frequency bins.

the EQ chip will give a reading how oftern the frequency apperas since the last reading.

The Value above the Trigger will be put into the selected data line. 
Example: FFT RED+FFT-Bri selected. 
Trigger set to 100, Reading = 130, the falue of RED is +30 (130-100). 
The value of Britness = Master Britnes(50) + 30 = 80. 

FFT-BRI & FFT-FPS adds onto the configured Master-BRI / FPS. 
MAX-BRI is capped at 255, MAX-FPS is capped at 100
